-- Stocks Advance in Europe on Irish Bailout; Banks, Mining Shares Lead Rally
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-11-22T08:04:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/stocks-advance-in-europe-on-irish-bailout-banks-mining-shares-lead-rally.html
European stocks rallied, rebounding 
from a two-week drop, after Ireland agreed to an international 
bailout to save its banks and prevent contagion across the 
region’s debt markets. U.S. stock-index futures and Asian 
equities rose.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index climbed 0.7 percent to
271.4 at 8:02 a.m. in London, as all 19 industry groups
advanced. Banks led the rally, as HSBC Holdings Plc gained 1
percent and Banco Santander SA climbed 1.5 percent. Rio Tinto
Group paced gains by basic-resource companies, jumping 1.4
percent.  Futures on the Standrad & Poor’s 500 Index expiring in
December rose 0.4 percent, while the MSCI Asia Pacific Index
gained 0.7 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
